# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Costa Brava Trip Planner — environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your keys. `.env` is gitignored — never
# commit real keys. The app is FULLY functional on seed data with NO keys; keys
# only add live photos, ratings, drive times, the interactive map, and the
# optional "suggest more" feature.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Google Maps Platform — a single key powering:
#   • Maps JavaScript API   (the interactive map)
#   • Places API (New)      (photos, ratings, hours, website, verification)
#   • Routes API            (drive time from your home base to each place)
# Create at https://console.cloud.google.com/ → enable those 3 APIs → Credentials.
# Restrict the key to HTTP referrers (your deploy domain + http://localhost:5173).
VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=

# Anthropic API key — OPTIONAL. Powers the Tier-3 "Suggest more places" feature
# (Claude + web_search). Every AI suggestion is re-verified against Google Places
# before it is ever shown; unverifiable suggestions are silently dropped.
# Get one at https://console.anthropic.com/ . Leave blank to disable the feature.
#
# NOTE: A browser-exposed key (VITE_ prefix) is visible to users. For a shared
# private device this is acceptable; to hide it, deploy the included serverless
# proxy (see README) and set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY there instead.
VITE_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Claude model used for live suggestions (optional override).
VITE_ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
